00:33:00,603 --> 00:33:05,650
was the housekeeper,
and her alibi has already been confirmed.

485
00:33:06,317 --> 00:33:08,486
According to statements
from people around him,

486
00:33:08,569 --> 00:33:11,906
the only person who knew the door code

487
00:33:11,990 --> 00:33:14,534
was Mr. Do Ra-ik.

488
00:33:15,326 --> 00:33:17,912
And as you can see,
there's no sign of forced entry.

489
00:33:18,413 --> 00:33:19,872
<i>Those crazy obsessive fangirls!</i>

490
00:33:19,956 --> 00:33:21,749
They even broke into my house recently.

491
00:33:22,458 --> 00:33:25,795
Meaning, on that night,

492
00:33:27,088 --> 00:33:31,592
the only people in this place
were the victim and the suspect.

493
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:36,472
I hear your client
is still claiming he's innocent.

494
00:33:36,556 --> 00:33:41,144
You and I both know how irrational

495
00:33:42,437 --> 00:33:43,688
{\an8}and reckless that is.

496
00:33:45,565 --> 00:33:47,483
So try to convince him…

497
00:33:52,989 --> 00:33:54,949
So annoyed.

498
00:33:55,033 --> 00:33:56,451
It stinks.

499
00:33:57,618 --> 00:33:58,661
Kwak Byung-gyun

500
00:34:07,462 --> 00:34:09,589
That won't do for me.

501
00:34:12,675 --> 00:34:18,264
I'm the type who actually enjoys
doing irrational, crazy things.

502
00:34:20,892 --> 00:34:23,061
See you at the warrant hearing.

503
00:34:31,819 --> 00:34:33,988
Interesting.

504
00:34:35,656 --> 00:34:36,908
Are you crazy?

505
00:34:49,879 --> 00:34:51,047
I mean,

506
00:34:51,130 --> 00:34:54,425
even if you're Maeng Se-na
the lone-wolf hyena, this is too much!

507
00:34:54,509 --> 00:34:56,761
You do know Attorney Hwang
advises Goldie, right?

508
00:34:56,844 --> 00:34:59,972
With the entertainment debating
whether to cut Do Ra-ik off,

509
00:35:00,056 --> 00:35:03,184
coming out with an innocence claim
from the same law firm is just--

510
00:35:03,267 --> 00:35:05,812
- Are you that afraid of Chief Kwak?
- Come on!

511
00:35:08,648 --> 00:35:09,524
Yes.

512
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:15,530
Because of that snake of a man,
I had to endure all that humiliation…

513
00:35:16,405 --> 00:35:19,283
You know exactly
why I turned down judgeships,

514
00:35:19,367 --> 00:35:22,537
prosecutor jobs, and every big law firm

515
00:35:22,620 --> 00:35:28,042
to join your tiny firm back when
you were barely surviving in Seocho.

516
00:35:31,129 --> 00:35:32,171
I don't know!

517
00:35:32,797 --> 00:35:35,174
You always bring that up
whenever things don't go your way.

518
00:35:35,258 --> 00:35:39,011
Kwak Jong-chul is going to twist this case
to his advantage again.

519
00:35:39,095 --> 00:35:41,681
He'll stir up the media,
get himself a friendly judge.

520
00:35:41,764 --> 00:35:43,975
And then, once again,
an innocent person will--

521
00:35:44,058 --> 00:35:46,894
No, I'm not listening!

522
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:51,023
There are too many inconsistencies
in this case.

523
00:35:51,858 --> 00:35:54,110
I haven't seen the case files yet,
so it's not clear,

524
00:35:54,193 --> 00:35:55,695
but I'm certain there's something.

525
00:35:55,778 --> 00:35:58,906
Why are you so hung up on this case?

526
00:35:58,990 --> 00:36:00,449
Do you have some kind of certainty?

527
00:36:02,493 --> 00:36:03,452
I just…

528
00:36:04,579 --> 00:36:06,455
There's something
I want to check for myself.

529
00:36:11,502 --> 00:36:15,047
I don't know! I can't do anything to help.

530
00:36:15,131 --> 00:36:17,633
And if something goes wrong,
it's all on you, okay?

531
00:36:17,717 --> 00:36:18,718
Yes.

532
00:36:18,801 --> 00:36:21,012
You can talk just fine.

533
00:36:25,766 --> 00:36:26,726
What do you need?

534
00:36:29,020 --> 00:36:30,313
Nothing.

535
00:36:30,396 --> 00:36:33,733
Just keep giving me free rein,
stay out of my way

536
00:36:33,816 --> 00:36:35,985
like you always do,
and let me work however I want.

537
00:36:41,532 --> 00:36:43,659
Knock it off.
What are you here to gawk at?

538
00:36:44,285 --> 00:36:47,330
The ones who can't work
always look for someone else's weakness.

539
00:36:48,039 --> 00:36:50,917
Ears perked up, hoping to catch something.

540
00:36:57,548 --> 00:37:00,509
You may have heard already,
I'll be handling Mr. Do Ra-ik's case.

541
00:37:00,593 --> 00:37:02,261
I need all related case files compiled.

542
00:37:02,345 --> 00:37:03,304
Sure.

543
00:37:13,147 --> 00:37:14,482
Come in.

544
00:37:20,363 --> 00:37:24,158
These are the notes
from Attorney Hwang's last meeting

545
00:37:24,242 --> 00:37:26,369
and the suspect's interview records.

546
00:37:26,452 --> 00:37:29,080
I thought they might be helpful.

547
00:37:33,209 --> 00:37:34,585
How did you get this?

548
00:37:34,669 --> 00:37:36,462
There's no way
he handed it over willingly.

549
00:37:39,674 --> 00:37:40,841
I stole it.

550
00:37:43,261 --> 00:37:44,720
I wanted to help.

551
00:37:46,264 --> 00:37:50,017
I'd like to become your legal assistant.

552
00:37:53,187 --> 00:37:56,565
I'm a fan of Gold Boys.

553
00:38:00,820 --> 00:38:01,988
Don't ever do this again.

554
00:38:02,071 --> 00:38:05,324
If something happens because of this,
I won't be able to protect you.

555
00:38:06,033 --> 00:38:07,868
- You can go now.
- Yes.

556
00:38:11,789 --> 00:38:12,957
Before the warrant hearing,

557
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:16,627
we only have the suspect's testimony,
no investigation records, so it's tough.

558
00:38:17,753 --> 00:38:21,048
Find me similar cases or precedents
where a not-guilty claim was upheld.

559
00:38:21,132 --> 00:38:22,341
As many as you can.

560
00:38:22,425 --> 00:38:26,679
And you can sign the NDA
and put it on my desk by tomorrow.

561
00:38:26,762 --> 00:38:27,805
Yes!

562
00:38:48,284 --> 00:38:50,703
Hey, did you get Jin-taek's number?

563
00:38:50,786 --> 00:38:53,205
Almost, he's going live today.

564
00:38:53,289 --> 00:38:58,085
- I'm going to call him right then.
- Nice.

565
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:06,093
You're Kim Hee-young, Choi Ha-neul, right?

566
00:39:07,636 --> 00:39:08,471
Who are you?

567
00:39:08,554 --> 00:39:10,681
Do we know you? Do you know this person?

568
00:39:12,850 --> 00:39:14,310
Hello, obsessive pests…

569
00:39:14,393 --> 00:39:16,937
I mean, obsessive fans. Nice to meet you.

570
00:39:17,021 --> 00:39:18,647
Mind if we have a little chat?

571
00:39:19,690 --> 00:39:23,402
- Who is she?
- I don't know.

572
00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:29,116
No, we are not!

573
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:30,785
Too loud, you.

574
00:39:32,495 --> 00:39:33,788
We're not obsessive fans.

575
00:39:33,871 --> 00:39:36,832
{\an8}We're TMB fans.

576
00:39:37,625 --> 00:39:39,668
<i>Hands off! Record it!</i>

577
00:39:39,752 --> 00:39:42,213
<i>- Get out!</i>
<i>- I'll call the police!</i>

578
00:39:42,296 --> 00:39:44,548
<i>- Oppa!</i>
- You still deny it?

579
00:39:44,632 --> 00:39:46,759
<i>How could you do this to your fans?</i>

580
00:39:46,842 --> 00:39:47,843
So what?

581
00:39:48,469 --> 00:39:52,473
Yeah, we snuck in, but he said it was fine
and told us to leave!

582
00:39:52,556 --> 00:39:54,392
Things are not fine anymore.

583
00:39:55,017 --> 00:39:58,562
A murder took place
in the very place you trespassed into.

584
00:39:58,646 --> 00:40:00,731
And I don't think
those two events are unrelated.

585
00:40:04,151 --> 00:40:05,903
What is she talking about?

586
00:40:05,986 --> 00:40:08,823
{\an8}That day Woo-seong ended up like that,

587
00:40:08,906 --> 00:40:11,325
{\an8}- we were tailing the TMB boys.
- Right.

588
00:40:12,034 --> 00:40:13,828
{\an8}How did you even find us?

589
00:40:13,911 --> 00:40:17,998
{\an8}Is it okay for you
to go after unrelated people like this?

590
00:40:18,082 --> 00:40:20,000
Well, whether there's a connection or not

591
00:40:20,084 --> 00:40:22,586
can change a lot
depending on the angle you look from.

592
00:40:24,463 --> 00:40:28,050
Not reporting it
doesn't make your crime any lighter.

593
00:40:28,134 --> 00:40:32,012
Being fans doesn't mean
you get to do whatever you want.

594
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:35,975
And I fully intend to make you understand

595
00:40:36,058 --> 00:40:38,686
just how serious your actions were.

596
00:40:40,604 --> 00:40:43,607
You've seen how this case
shows up in real-time headlines

597
00:40:43,691 --> 00:40:45,401
every morning and night, right?

598
00:40:45,484 --> 00:40:47,736
With the case blowing up like this,

599
00:40:47,820 --> 00:40:51,574
what do you think will happen
when reporters find out

600
00:40:51,657 --> 00:40:54,076
two people trespassed
into Mr. Do Ra-ik's house?

601
00:40:56,370 --> 00:40:58,247
They'll love it, right?

602
00:40:59,623 --> 00:41:04,587
I'll file the lawsuits one at a time,
at a very slow pace

603
00:41:04,670 --> 00:41:07,131
and watch the attention grow even bigger.

604
00:41:08,215 --> 00:41:12,011
Then it won't be him appearing on TV
in real time anymore.

605
00:41:12,094 --> 00:41:14,180
It'll be you guys.

606
00:41:14,263 --> 00:41:16,891
And the forums will go crazy
digging up your information.

607
00:41:18,017 --> 00:41:19,477
People will be curious.

608
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:22,730
Like, who are these girls,

609
00:41:22,813 --> 00:41:26,609
and how were they sneaking in and out
of his house without anyone noticing?

610
00:41:26,692 --> 00:41:29,069
- And how did they know the passcode?
- It's not…

611
00:41:31,113 --> 00:41:32,698
I wasn't asking you to answer.

612
00:41:33,282 --> 00:41:36,827
All I have to do is sit back and wait.

613
00:41:39,788 --> 00:41:43,584
The reporters will get
all the answers for me anyway.

614
00:41:44,126 --> 00:41:45,794
Relentlessly.

615
00:41:49,757 --> 00:41:50,591
Excuse me!

616
00:41:53,469 --> 00:41:56,472
We only went there
because someone told us about it.

617
00:41:56,555 --> 00:41:58,224
It was just curiosity.

618
00:42:02,186 --> 00:42:03,020
How?

619
00:42:04,522 --> 00:42:05,523
It's…

620
00:42:09,985 --> 00:42:14,490
<i>The security guards switch shifts</i>
<i>from 11:50 p.m. to 12:00 a.m.</i>

621
00:42:19,203 --> 00:42:20,913
<i>That's when we go in.</i>

622
00:42:23,457 --> 00:42:26,168
<i>We already know</i>
<i>all the CCTV locations anyway,</i>

623
00:42:26,252 --> 00:42:29,296
<i>so avoiding them is a piece of cake.</i>

624
00:42:46,522 --> 00:42:49,191
<i>We just wait for the right moment,</i>
<i>and when the door opens, bam!</i>

625
00:42:49,275 --> 00:42:52,403
<i>We slip in, and that's it. Game over.</i>

626
00:42:58,075 --> 00:43:00,160
<i>Because of resident privacy,</i>

627
00:43:00,244 --> 00:43:02,663
<i>there are no CCTVs</i>
<i>in the hallways or stairwells.</i>

628
00:43:15,759 --> 00:43:19,805
<i>And the last step is waiting on the stairs</i>
<i>with the motion-sensor light disabled.</i>

629
00:43:19,888 --> 00:43:23,183
<i>If it turns on by accident, we're screwed.</i>

630
00:43:24,351 --> 00:43:27,313
<i>So we set everything up</i>
<i>before Ra-ik gets home and wait.</i>

631
00:43:27,855 --> 00:43:30,941
<i>That way, we can safely watch</i>
<i>and figure out the passcode.</i>

632
00:43:38,699 --> 00:43:42,453
<i>Once we get the passcode,</i>
<i>we wait for a day he's out</i>

633
00:43:42,536 --> 00:43:45,539
<i>and the housekeeper's off, then we go in.</i>

634
00:43:45,623 --> 00:43:47,541
<i>As long as he doesn't change the code,</i>

635
00:43:47,625 --> 00:43:49,918
<i>we can come and go whenever we want,</i>

636
00:43:50,586 --> 00:43:52,171
<i>as long as we don't get caught.</i>

637
00:43:54,840 --> 00:43:56,634
You two are real professionals.

638
00:43:57,760 --> 00:44:00,888
So after figuring out
the passcode to his place,

639
00:44:01,472 --> 00:44:04,391
you went back on another day,
snuck into his house

640
00:44:04,475 --> 00:44:05,809
and he caught you?

641
00:44:05,893 --> 00:44:08,687
- That day, you filmed the video of him?
- Yes.

642
00:44:09,855 --> 00:44:11,982
It's because he called us cockroaches.

643
00:44:12,066 --> 00:44:13,651
- Right?
- Yes.

644
00:44:15,194 --> 00:44:16,195
But…

645
00:44:16,779 --> 00:44:19,031
{\an8}Did he really kill Woo-seong?

646
00:44:19,114 --> 00:44:21,867
That's your big question, you stalker?

647
00:44:21,950 --> 00:44:24,244
I told you, we're not stalkers!

648
00:44:24,828 --> 00:44:27,539
We did it because we love him!

649
00:44:28,749 --> 00:44:30,501
Isn't that what love is?

650
00:44:30,584 --> 00:44:34,338
Wanting to get closer,
wanting to see him,

651
00:44:34,421 --> 00:44:36,548
- wanting to take care of him more.
- No.

652
00:44:37,174 --> 00:44:39,176
That's not love. That's hunting.

653
00:44:40,010 --> 00:44:41,136
Because it was fun,

654
00:44:41,220 --> 00:44:44,098
threatening someone's life
and making them suffer.

655
00:44:44,181 --> 00:44:45,140
Violently.

656
00:44:46,809 --> 00:44:50,396
If you truly loved him,
you could never do something like that.

657
00:44:55,442 --> 00:44:57,277
Real love is…

658
00:45:00,489 --> 00:45:04,993
<i>watching the path he walks</i>
<i>from far, far away…</i>

659
00:45:06,870 --> 00:45:08,247
<i>supporting him,</i>

660
00:45:09,748 --> 00:45:11,333
<i>and wishing</i>

661
00:45:12,418 --> 00:45:14,002
<i>for his happiness…</i>

662
00:45:16,255 --> 00:45:17,589
<i>with all your heart.</i>

663
00:45:17,673 --> 00:45:19,466
Bring him back to life!

664
00:45:19,550 --> 00:45:21,593
- Bring him back!
- Bring him back!

665
00:45:21,677 --> 00:45:24,304
Execute Do Ra-ik!

666
00:45:24,388 --> 00:45:25,806
- Execute him!
- Execute him!

667
00:45:35,858 --> 00:45:39,236
- Here he comes!
- Just say one word!

668
00:45:39,319 --> 00:45:41,280
How do you feel right now?

669
00:45:41,363 --> 00:45:42,865
Keep your head up.

670
00:45:42,948 --> 00:45:44,158
COURT

671
00:45:46,243 --> 00:45:48,912
{\an8}You look like guilty
if you keep your head down.

672
00:45:49,538 --> 00:45:51,540
{\an8}Lift your head, and stand tall.

673
00:45:53,959 --> 00:45:54,793
I don't know.

674
00:45:57,463 --> 00:45:58,797
I don't remember.

675
00:46:01,091 --> 00:46:03,093
No matter how hard I try,
I can't remember.

676
00:46:06,054 --> 00:46:07,347
It wasn't me.

677
00:46:09,099 --> 00:46:10,392
It really wasn't.

678
00:46:14,062 --> 00:46:15,481
But what if it was?

679
00:46:17,149 --> 00:46:19,443
What if I was the one
who did that to Woo-seong…

680
00:46:20,486 --> 00:46:21,778
Mr. Do Ra-ik.

681
00:46:24,531 --> 00:46:25,449
Mr. Do Ra-ik.

682
00:46:31,538 --> 00:46:33,457
{\an8}As long as I'm representing you,

683
00:46:33,540 --> 00:46:35,876
you will be found innocent.

684
00:46:35,959 --> 00:46:38,253
I'll make sure of it. Understood?

685
00:46:40,547 --> 00:46:43,884
So repeat after me, "I, Do Ra-ik."

686
00:46:46,845 --> 00:46:49,056
I said repeat after me, "I, Do Ra-ik."

687
00:46:50,516 --> 00:46:51,433
I, Do Ra-ik.

688
00:46:52,184 --> 00:46:54,978
"Did not kill Kang Woo-seong."

689
00:46:59,983 --> 00:47:01,818
Did not kill Kang Woo-seong.

690
00:47:01,902 --> 00:47:05,989
{\an8}"I do not admit to killing
Kang Woo-seong."

691
00:47:07,699 --> 00:47:12,204
I do not admit to killing Kang Woo-seong.

692
00:47:16,458 --> 00:47:18,710
Counsel, please state your position.

693
00:47:26,343 --> 00:47:27,594
Your Honor,

694
00:47:27,678 --> 00:47:31,139
the prosecution's sole basis
for labeling the defendant a murderer

695
00:47:31,223 --> 00:47:36,812
is just one claim that no third party
entered the scene of the crime.

696
00:47:36,895 --> 00:47:40,065
However, two weeks before the incident,

697
00:47:40,148 --> 00:47:42,943
the defendant was the victim
of an illegal home intrusion

698
00:47:43,026 --> 00:47:44,653
committed by obsessive fans.

699
00:47:44,736 --> 00:47:48,991
Because of his status as a public figure,
an official police report was not filed,

700
00:47:49,074 --> 00:47:51,910
but the fact of the illegal intrusion
by obsessive fans

701
00:47:51,994 --> 00:47:54,830
has already been sufficiently
and objectively proven.

702
00:47:54,913 --> 00:47:56,456
Therefore, the prosecution's premise

703
00:47:56,540 --> 00:47:58,584
that no third party entered the residence

704
00:47:58,667 --> 00:48:00,460
has effectively lost
its credibility, and--

705
00:48:00,544 --> 00:48:01,962
That claim is unverified.

706
00:48:02,879 --> 00:48:05,966
It's the prosecution
that is making unverified claims.

707
00:48:07,801 --> 00:48:09,928
Your Honor, the prosecution has stated

708
00:48:10,012 --> 00:48:13,390
that all forensic processing
of the defendant's home is complete.

709
00:48:13,473 --> 00:48:15,726
But according to the warrant application,

710
00:48:15,809 --> 00:48:18,145
there is no mention whatsoever
of the weapon presumed

711
00:48:18,228 --> 00:48:21,106
to have been used in the crime.

712
00:48:21,607 --> 00:48:24,318
Prosecutor,
do you have an explanation for this?

713
00:48:24,401 --> 00:48:25,861
Regarding that,

714
00:48:25,944 --> 00:48:28,071
it's still under investigation.

715
00:48:28,155 --> 00:48:29,823
I can't disclose any specific details.

716
00:48:30,365 --> 00:48:35,078
But the forensic results show
that there were no signs of external--

717
00:48:35,162 --> 00:48:37,789
Your Honor,
on the night of the incident,

718
00:48:37,873 --> 00:48:40,917
record-breaking heavy rain
began to fall at midnight.

719
00:48:41,001 --> 00:48:44,504
Therefore, the possibility that traces
of an intrusion were erased by the rain

720
00:48:44,588 --> 00:48:46,882
- must be carefully reconsidered.
- Your Honor,

721
00:48:46,965 --> 00:48:49,509
the defense is engaging
in baseless speculation.

722
00:48:49,593 --> 00:48:53,305
It is the prosecution's responsibility
to prove whether it is speculation or not.

723
00:48:55,974 --> 00:48:58,018
According to the defendant's
interrogation record,

724
00:48:58,101 --> 00:49:00,937
{\an8}<i>they repeatedly questioned him</i>
<i>with things like,</i>

725
00:49:01,021 --> 00:49:03,357
{\an8}<i>"There were signs</i>
<i>that the place had been searched.</i>

726
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:05,484
{\an8}<i>What exactly were you looking for?"</i>

727
00:49:05,567 --> 00:49:10,489
{\an8}This means the presence of search traces
at the scene cannot be excluded.

728
00:49:11,573 --> 00:49:13,283
In general, search traces

729
00:49:13,367 --> 00:49:17,371
are marks left when an offender is trying
to find or hide a particular item.

730
00:49:17,454 --> 00:49:21,041
So they can serve as strong evidence
that someone other than the defendant,

731
00:49:21,124 --> 00:49:25,545
specifically, someone unfamiliar
with the space

732
00:49:25,629 --> 00:49:28,507
was present at the crime scene.

733
00:49:28,590 --> 00:49:32,219
Prosecutor, was any such trace
found at the scene?

734
00:49:36,181 --> 00:49:38,058
Yes, there was.

735
00:49:39,893 --> 00:49:41,520
Your Honor,

736
00:49:41,603 --> 00:49:43,897
under the fundamental principles
of criminal procedure,

737
00:49:43,980 --> 00:49:48,360
a guilty verdict must be based on evidence
that leaves no room for reasonable doubt.

738
00:49:48,944 --> 00:49:51,613
Therefore, since the prosecution
has failed to present

739
00:49:51,697 --> 00:49:54,074
any clear evidence proving
the defendant's alleged crime,

740
00:49:54,157 --> 00:49:58,954
the request for an arrest warrant
to detain the defendant must be denied.

741
00:50:00,163 --> 00:50:01,957
Accordingly,

742
00:50:02,040 --> 00:50:05,085
based on the presumption of innocence,
the defense strongly urges

743
00:50:05,168 --> 00:50:07,421
that the defendant not be detained.

744
00:50:16,972 --> 00:50:18,056
That stings.

745
00:50:22,060 --> 00:50:25,313
You're throwing counterpunches
from the very first round.

746
00:50:25,397 --> 00:50:26,231
Pardon?

747
00:50:29,317 --> 00:50:30,444
A counterpunch

748
00:50:31,862 --> 00:50:33,989
is when you strike back
against an incoming attack.

749
00:50:34,573 --> 00:50:36,908
I didn't really see anything
I'd call an attack.

750
00:50:36,992 --> 00:50:38,827
So that was just a couple of jabs?

751
00:50:38,910 --> 00:50:40,162
That's right.

752
00:50:40,245 --> 00:50:41,830
Compare them next time,

753
00:50:41,913 --> 00:50:44,458
how a jab differs from a counterpunch.

754
00:50:45,834 --> 00:50:47,586
I'm going to knock you out then.

755
00:51:02,267 --> 00:51:04,770
How do you overlook
something that important?

756
00:51:04,853 --> 00:51:08,607
If they didn't report it,
how would I know?

757
00:51:09,232 --> 00:51:12,986
- This just got complicated, seriously.
- It's fine.

758
00:51:13,069 --> 00:51:15,906
It was just a blank.
It fired, so that's good enough.

759
00:51:19,910 --> 00:51:21,244
{\an8}He talks well.

760
00:51:39,638 --> 00:51:41,890
The results will come out later.

761
00:51:43,350 --> 00:51:46,561
You can go home now
since the forensic work is done.

762
00:51:48,230 --> 00:51:50,899
Do you have anyone to contact?
Someone you trust.

763
00:51:50,982 --> 00:51:52,609
I'll have them come pick you up.

764
00:52:03,078 --> 00:52:07,123
{\an8}<i>The arrest warrant for singer Do Ra-ik</i>
<i>has been dismissed.</i>

765
00:52:07,207 --> 00:52:10,794
{\an8}<i>In today's closed warrant review hearing,</i>

766
00:52:10,877 --> 00:52:15,549
{\an8}<i>the court determined that he doesn't pose</i>
<i>a risk of destroying evidence or fleeing.</i>

767
00:52:16,091 --> 00:52:18,802
{\an8}<i>As a result of this decision,</i>
<i>he will remain out of custody</i>

768
00:52:18,885 --> 00:52:21,638
<i>as the investigation continues.</i>

769
00:52:21,721 --> 00:52:24,307
<i>However, the case is not over yet.</i>

770
00:52:24,391 --> 00:52:29,020
<i>The prosecution is working</i>
<i>to secure additional evidence</i>

771
00:52:29,104 --> 00:52:32,899
<i>to determine the cause of Kang's death</i>
<i>and to uncover the full circumstances…</i>

772
00:52:53,503 --> 00:52:54,671
Pull over for a moment.

773
00:53:32,500 --> 00:53:34,711
MURDERER

774
00:54:45,407 --> 00:54:48,535
Why are you being like that to Jae-hee?

775
00:54:49,119 --> 00:54:51,079
He cares about you so much.

776
00:54:51,162 --> 00:54:52,914
But why doesn't he call me?

777
00:54:53,498 --> 00:54:56,543
It's not that he doesn't like you.
Just hurry up and open it.

778
00:54:56,626 --> 00:54:57,669
- Hungry, right?
- Yes.

779
00:54:58,503 --> 00:55:01,631
I'm going in first!

780
00:56:13,495 --> 00:56:15,872
- You still can't stay on pitch.
- Then you do it.

781
00:56:21,336 --> 00:56:23,671
You try it.

782
00:56:26,049 --> 00:56:29,260
Come on, I searched so much for it…

783
00:56:29,969 --> 00:56:32,097
I've got this.

784
00:56:33,973 --> 00:56:36,976
I told you it's not.

785
00:56:37,060 --> 00:56:39,521
- Isn't this how it's supposed to be done?
- No.

786
00:56:46,486 --> 00:56:50,073
- You have to lift your pinky!
- All right.

787
00:56:50,156 --> 00:56:51,699
I'll try again.

788
00:57:58,016 --> 00:57:58,975
Did you wake up?

789
00:58:01,603 --> 00:58:04,647
That's a relief.
I thought you might not wake up.

790
00:58:07,984 --> 00:58:09,527
It's good to see you again,

791
00:58:10,820 --> 00:58:12,155
Mr. Do Ra-ik.

792
00:58:12,739 --> 00:58:14,240
Welcome…

793
00:58:17,202 --> 00:58:18,244
to my home.

794
00:59:14,175 --> 00:59:15,927
{\an8}<i>I'm Do Ra-ik's lawyer right now.</i>

795
00:59:16,010 --> 00:59:18,012
{\an8}<i>I have to protect my client to the end.</i>

796
00:59:18,638 --> 00:59:20,431
{\an8}<i>Is that really the only reason?</i>

797
00:59:21,140 --> 00:59:22,475
{\an8}<i>Ugh, Maeng-byeon, seriously.</i>

798
00:59:22,559 --> 00:59:23,643
{\an8}Aren't you scared?

799
00:59:23,726 --> 00:59:24,602
{\an8}Punish Do Ra-ik.

800
00:59:24,686 --> 00:59:27,397
{\an8}<i>Given the distance, you should have been</i>
<i>back within 20 minutes at the latest.</i>

801
00:59:27,480 --> 00:59:30,233
{\an8}You're hiding something from me, right?
What is it?

802
00:59:30,316 --> 00:59:31,526
{\an8}<i>Will you even trust me?</i>

803
00:59:31,609 --> 00:59:32,986
{\an8}Until the end.

804
00:59:33,486 --> 00:59:35,196
{\an8}I'll stay by your side.

805
00:59:35,280 --> 00:59:37,031
{\an8}<i>I will find my memory back somehow.</i>

806
00:59:37,949 --> 00:59:39,158
{\an8}<i>No matter what.</i>

807
00:59:40,493 --> 00:59:45,498
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Kim Soyeon

